Legal Calculus 4.5 — Enhanced Modules — Module 26
📘 Legal Calculus — Module 26

Summary Judgment Skeleton — Separate Facts & Law

⚖️ Core Message

Win or survive with clean fact statements and pinpoint cites.
📖 Lesson Content

1. File a Separate Statement of Facts (SSOF) with one fact per paragraph and record pin‑cites.
2. Move arguments out of the SSOF; keep law in the brief.
3. Dispute facts with specific citations; avoid 'disputed as to form' rhetoric.
4. Attach key exhibits with Bates/page IDs used in the SSOF.
📝 Assignment

Draft a 1‑page SSOF with 10 numbered facts and pin‑cites to exhibits or deposition pages.
✅ Model Response

SEPARATE STATEMENT OF FACTS (excerpt)

1. USPS delivered Plaintiff’s motion on July 31, 2025 (Ex. A at 1).

2. The Clerk docketed the motion on Aug. 2, 2025 (Dkt 18 at 2).

 

💡 Reflection Summary

Facts in one lane; law in the other.
🎨 Visual Concept

Two parallel lanes labeled FACTS and LAW.
